# ============================================================================
# _skystreamer — zsh completion for **skystreamer** —
#                 FyraLabs/skystreamer, the **AT Protocol firehose
#                 collector** that subscribes to the Bluesky relay
#                 `bsky.network` (or any other AT Protocol relay
#                 implementing the `com.atproto.sync.subscribeRepos`
#                 websocket endpoint), parses every repo-commit
#                 event into typed `app.bsky.feed.Post` records,
#                 and streams the result to one of four
#                 configurable exporters:  SurrealDB (default),
#                 JSONL append-only file, CSV append-only file, or
#                 a dry-run logger.  Used as the data-ingest leg of
#                 analytics pipelines that operate on the full
#                 firehose at the ~600 events/sec sustained rate
#                 the Bluesky network produces.  Rust=168 OPENING
#                 leg of new Axis 113 (AT Protocol / ATProto /
#                 Bluesky) via the canonical Rust AT Protocol SDK
#                 **atrium-api** + **atrium-xrpc-client**.
# ============================================================================
#
# UPSTREAM
#   Repository : https://github.com/FyraLabs/skystreamer
#   Maintainer : Cappy Ishihara  (Fyra Labs; same author also
#                 ships the `skystreamer` library crate that this
#                 binary builds on, plus the `gbif` Rust client +
#                 several other small Rust libraries)
#   License    : MIT
