# WHAT IT IS
#   Bluesky's AT Protocol exposes a `com.atproto.sync.subscribeRepos`
#   websocket endpoint at `wss://bsky.network` (and at every other
#   relay / mirror in the federated AT Protocol network) that
#   streams the **complete firehose of repo-commit events** for
#   every user on the network.  Each event is a CBOR-encoded
#   commit frame containing one or more DAG-CBOR record ops
#   (`com.atproto.repo.applyWrites`-style creates, updates, deletes)
#   plus the IPLD blocks referenced by those ops, packaged in a
#   CAR (Content-Addressable aRchive) blob.
#
#   `skystreamer` connects to this firehose, dispatches each frame
#   to a tokio task that decodes the CAR + extracts every
#   `app.bsky.feed.post` typed record (via atrium-api's typed
#   lexicon bindings), and hands the parsed `Post` to a swappable
#   exporter trait.  Built-in exporters:
#
#     • surrealdb    Write each post + author profile into a
#                    SurrealDB instance (`ws://localhost:8000` by
#                    default; authentication via Token / Root /
#                    Namespace credential modes; configurable
#                    `--namespace` + `--database`).  This is the
#                    default — drop into a SurrealDB query shell
#                    and run SurrealQL over the live firehose.
#     • jsonl        Append each post as a single line of JSON
#                    to `--file-path <PATH>`.  Pipeline-friendly
#                    for jq / fx / dasel / yq consumers.
#     • csv          Append each post as a CSV row to
#                    `--file-path <PATH>`.
#     • dry-run      Log to stdout, write nothing.  Useful for
#                    measuring the sustained ingest rate of the
#                    target relay or for sanity-checking that
#                    the subscription is working.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from skystreamer-bin/src/config.rs
#                       `Config` struct + flattened
#                       `SurrealDbConn` + `FileExporterOptions`
#                       structs; extracted via
#                       raw.githubusercontent.com fetch of
#                       skystreamer-bin/src/config.rs)
#
#   skystreamer [OPTIONS]
#
#   Options:
#     -h, --help                     Show help
#     -V, --version                  Print version
#
#     -R, --atproto-relay <HOST>     AT Protocol relay to subscribe
#                                    to (just the bare hostname;
#                                    `wss://` prefix added
#                                    automatically)
#                                    [default: bsky.network]
#                                    [env: ATPROTO_RELAY]
#
#     -E, --exporter <TYPE>          Exporter backend
#                                    [default: surrealdb]
#                                    [values: jsonl, csv,
#                                     surrealdb, dry-run]
#                                    [env: EXPORTER]
#
#     -o, --file-path <PATH>         Path to the output file (for
#                                    jsonl / csv exporters)
#                                    [required if exporter is
#                                     jsonl or csv]
#                                    [env: FILE_EXPORT_PATH]
#
#   SurrealDB exporter options:
#     -e, --surreal-endpoint <URL>   SurrealDB endpoint
#                                    [default: ws://localhost:8000]
#                                    [required if exporter is
#                                     surrealdb]
#                                    [env: SURREAL_ENDPOINT]
#     -a, --auth-type <TYPE>         Authentication type
#                                    [values: token, root,
#                                     namespace]
#                                    [env: SURREAL_AUTH_TYPE]
#     -k, --token <TOKEN>            Token for authentication
#                                    [required if auth-type is
#                                     token]
#                                    [env: SURREAL_TOKEN]
#     -u, --username <USER>          Username for authentication
#                                    [required if auth-type is
#                                     root or namespace]
#                                    [env: SURREAL_USER]
#     -p, --password <PASS>          Password for authentication
#                                    [required if auth-type is
#                                     root or namespace]
#                                    [env: SURREAL_PASS]
#     -n, --namespace <NS>           SurrealDB namespace
#                                    [default: bsky.network]
#                                    [env: SURREAL_NAMESPACE]
#     -d, --database <DB>            SurrealDB database
#                                    [default: bsky]
#                                    [env: SURREAL_DATABASE]
#     -f, --fetch-user-data <BOOL>   Fetch user-profile data from
#                                    ATProto on each post
#                                    [default: true]
#                                    [env: FETCH_USER_DATA]
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   `skystreamer-bin` declares **direct** dependencies on
#   `atrium-api = "0.24.8"` (with the `tokio` feature) and
#   `atrium-xrpc-client` (with the `reqwest` feature) in its
#   `Cargo.toml` (verified via `gh api repos/FyraLabs/skystreamer/
#   contents/skystreamer-bin/Cargo.toml`).
#
#   `sugyan/atrium` is **THE canonical Rust AT Protocol SDK** —
#   the Rust counterpart to `bluesky-social/indigo` (Go) and
#   `bluesky-social/atproto` `@atproto/api` (TS/JS) — and ships
#   as a multi-crate workspace:
#
#     • `atrium-api`         (the typed lexicon-derived Rust
#                            bindings — every typed `app.bsky.*`,
#                            `com.atproto.*`, `tools.ozone.*`,
#                            `chat.bsky.*` record, query, and
#                            procedure as a Rust type with
#                            full serde round-trip;  produced by
#                            the `atrium-codegen` build step from
#                            the canonical lexicon JSON specs in
#                            `bluesky-social/atproto/lexicons/`)
#     • `atrium-xrpc`        (the typed XRPC wire-format protocol
#                            client trait with typed `Method`,
#                            typed request/response framing)
#     • `atrium-xrpc-client` (the concrete reqwest-backed XRPC
#                            transport)
#     • `atrium-common`      (shared traits — `Store`, `Cache`,
#                            etc.)
#     • `atrium-identity`    (DID + handle resolver — typed
#                            `did:plc:*` and `did:web:*`
#                            resolution against the canonical
#                            PLC directory at plc.directory)
#     • `atrium-oauth`       (the AT Protocol OAuth 2.0 client
#                            implementation with DPoP support
#                            for the AT Protocol's "lambda
#                            consumer with PKCE + DPoP-bound
#                            access token" flow)
#     • `atrium-ipld`        (DAG-CBOR + CID typed wrappers,
#                            re-exporting `ipld-core` for
#                            compatibility)
#
#   `atrium-api` exposes the typed lexicon model — every Bluesky
#   record kind has a typed Rust struct + a typed agent method
#   path that mirrors the lexicon's namespaced ID:
#
#     • `agent.api.app.bsky.feed.get_timeline(params)` →
#       `OutputData { feed: Vec<FeedViewPost>, cursor }`
#     • `agent.api.app.bsky.feed.get_author_feed(params)` →
#       `OutputData { feed, cursor }`
#     • `agent.api.app.bsky.feed.get_post_thread(params)` →
#       `OutputData { thread: PostThreadView }`
#     • `agent.api.app.bsky.actor.get_profile(params)` →
#       `OutputData { ProfileViewDetailed }`
#     • `agent.api.app.bsky.actor.search_actors(params)` →
#       `OutputData { actors: Vec<ProfileView>, cursor }`
#     • `agent.api.app.bsky.notification.list_notifications(...)`
#     • `agent.api.com.atproto.identity.resolve_handle(...)`
#     • `agent.api.com.atproto.repo.create_record(...)` /
#       `.put_record` / `.delete_record` / `.list_records` /
#       `.get_record` / `.apply_writes` / `.upload_blob`
#     • `agent.api.com.atproto.sync.subscribe_repos(params)` —
#       the firehose endpoint that `skystreamer` subscribes to
#     • `agent.api.com.atproto.sync.get_blob(...)` /
#       `.list_blobs(...)` / `.get_repo(...)` (CAR archive
#       download for full-repo backfills) /
#       `.list_repos(...)` (relay-wide repo enumeration)
#     • `agent.api.com.atproto.moderation.create_report(...)`
#     • `agent.api.com.atproto.label.query_labels(...)` /
#       `.subscribe_labels(...)`
#     • `agent.api.tools.ozone.moderation.emit_event(...)` /
#       `.query_events(...)` / `.query_statuses(...)` /
#       `.get_record(...)` / `.get_repo(...)` (the Ozone
#       moderation back-office API used by Bluesky's internal
#       moderation team + every third-party labeler such as
#       blacksky-algorithms/rsky-labeler)
#     • `agent.api.chat.bsky.convo.send_message(...)` /
#       `.get_convo(...)` / `.list_convos(...)` (the typed
#       DMs surface introduced in Bluesky's 2024 chat rollout)
#     • Every `app.bsky.feed.post::Record`,
#       `app.bsky.feed.like::Record`,
#       `app.bsky.feed.repost::Record`,
#       `app.bsky.graph.follow::Record`,
#       `app.bsky.graph.block::Record`,
#       `app.bsky.graph.list::Record`,
#       `app.bsky.graph.listitem::Record`,
#       `app.bsky.graph.listblock::Record`,
#       `app.bsky.actor.profile::Record`,
#       `app.bsky.feed.generator::Record` (custom feeds),
#       `app.bsky.feed.threadgate::Record`,
#       `app.bsky.labeler.service::Record`,
#       `app.bsky.feed.postgate::Record`,
#       `app.bsky.notification.declaration::Record`, and
#       `chat.bsky.actor.declaration::Record` Record-discriminated-
#       union variant with typed inner fields
#     • Typed `string::Did`, `string::Handle`, `string::AtUri`,
#       `string::Cid`, `string::Datetime`, `string::Nsid`
#       NewType wrappers with format validation enforced at
#       deserialize time
#
#   `sugyan/atrium` ecosystem powers every serious Rust AT
#   Protocol application in production: rsky (the Black Sky
#   Algorithms ATProto stack at 669+ ★ — rsky-pds the PDS
